1. Definitions

   "Official release" means a binary or source package published by
   the copyright holder through the official GitHub repository at
   https://github.com/Alysoun/PrevueSync or through other channels
   the copyright holder expressly designates as official (for example,
   a GitHub Release asset attached to a tagged version). A build you
   compile locally from source, an unofficial mirror, or a modified
   fork is not an official release unless the copyright holder
   designates it as such in writing.

   "Internal business use" means use of PrevueSync within a single
   organization — including its employees and contractors — to sync
   that organization's own data on systems it owns or controls.
   Internal business use is for the organization's own operations, not
   for offering sync or backup services to outside customers.

   Example (permitted under License A): A consulting firm with fifty
   employees installs PrevueSync on staff workstations to sync
   internal project folders and tooling the firm controls.

   Example (requires License B): That same firm offers a paid
   "PrevueSync-powered backup" or managed sync service to external
   clients, or redistributes PrevueSync as part of a product it sells.

